Properties.Text: Player is introduced to spices
Receive units and food after defeating previous war chef
Receive Bog Hard-Weeds and more food
Introduction - Peasants only battle
Player is introduced to warriors

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Nothing smells like victory, Lord! Blood-soaked fur and dung-stained soil!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Our looty-rats rummaged through the enemy camp, Lord! Rattapurna's bosom showers us with golden milk!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: They have found sack upon sack of Firemander Salts! Spike the food with it Lord, and our warriors will wield weapons of pure flame!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Rattan, the fat fool, did not give his moblings the Firemander Salts.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Make sure the spice sacks find their way to our food stores, General.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Nasty work, hunting firemanders to grind their bones to salts.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: A job fit for a gods-forsaken-prisoner! Better to hunt in Magma Marshes then to toil away in dark and stuffy mines. Fresh air and all...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yes, of course my Lord! Sacks will be accounted for, the spice ready to spike the food!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Rattapurna's will, my Lord! Otherwise, the battle might've been in Glut's favor!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Though, Lord, not all of the looty-rats returned from the pillage. A few reached their grubby paws into the Salt sacks!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: They were never found again. But there were piles of ash scattered around...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: No spice saves you now. I bring full might of my mobling horde now!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: How does one so fat skulk around so nimbly?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Don't know when to give up, Rattan?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: We have your Firemander Salts! Your numbers will melt away.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Fool! Won't be my moblings that melt away.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Rattan will be Divine King of all ratkin!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Only weak ratkin speak insults! My immensity is Rattapurna's blessing!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Sons of Rattan! Kill today and you will feast! Feast! Battlefield awaits us, War Chef!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: War Chef 3: Battle 4

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: stabby rats get

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: archers get

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: to battle!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: The fat fool Glut is dead, my Lord! Killed himself after the battle was lost.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: And Rattapurna's bosom spills the milk of fortune on us, Lord! More of our stabby-rats found their way to our army, along with a wagon of food.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: But, what is this?! What's causing that ruckus?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Lord! Lord! We fought for Glut, but he failed us! His immensity was not enough.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Allow us to serve you, Lord! To eat from your cauldron and kill for you!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: We really should get better guards...

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: We always need more meat shie-I mean troops!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Fight for me moblings and my food is your food!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: You were Glut's ratkin. If anyone tries to betray me, they will serve as kindling for the cauldron-fire!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Our lives are your lives, Lord, by Rattapurna's plentiful bosom!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Betray? Never, Lord! May our tails wither and die. We are your ratkin!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Our lives are yours to waste, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord! Lord! A bodyguard bearing the sickle crest is approaching, requesting parley!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: I have no interest in talking. Send them away.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: A small part of enemy forces, coming to be killed like sheep? Yes, please!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: A... sickle crest?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Always open for negotiation.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Dare I say, Lord, we should work on your heraldry skills once the war is done!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yes, Lord! Black sickle on a pus-yellow field.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: The crest belongs to Field Marshal Toothsy! The War Chef might even be among his honor guard.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: A cunning plan, Lord! Warriors are already on their way!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: My Lord... The warriors failed. Field Marshal's bodyguard ran away before we could engage.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: I'm afraid that old rotten Toothsy will be most displeased, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Smartest of moves, Lord! Why would we exchange words when we can exchange blows?

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Here they come, Lord! Rattapurna's tits! Field Marshal Toothsy is with them!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: War Ts-ts-ts-ef! Surrender your for-ts-ts-ts-es! My army of stabby-rats vastly outnumbers yours. No need to waste unne-ts-ts-ts-essary lives!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: If you ts-ts-ts-hoose to surrender, I'll make your death qui-ts-ts-ts-k and painless.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: My word, as War Te-ts-ts-ef!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Toothsy's forces gather, Lord! A battle is upon us!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Counter-offer: how about you stab yourself in the gut and die, slowly?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: This negotiation makes less sense then your speech, Toothsy.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: This meeting could've been a letter, Field Marshal.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: I won't stand being insulted!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: Most unwise, I see!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: I did my duty as the offi-ts-ts-ts-er of the realm. Now, my stabby-rats will ha-ts-ts-ts-k you all to death!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: You did it, Lord! You did it!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: No one has beaten the Field Marshal in a pitch battle since... since...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Anyhow! As customary, our looty-rats have pillaged the enemy camp. Sacks of food and pellets of Bog Hard-Weeds were discovered!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: There were some yellowish bulbs in the stacks, but worry not, Lord! I tested the spice on some moblings.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Sure enough, their skin hardened like stone and no blade could pierce it. Oh, stabby-rats tried!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Have it sent to the cooks, General.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: What about those yellowish bulbs? Bog weed should not have those.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Excellent work, Ratso! I might make you into a War Chef once I am king.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: No no! I live only to serve, Lord! But...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: I am sure it is nothing! Though some of those moblings projectile-vomited all over the camp.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Who knows? Maybe puke-missiles can be useful as well? If only those moblings weren't exhausted as a side effect...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yes, Lord! But...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Lord! Heralds with Field Marshal's crest are coming to see you!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Lord! Field Marshal's army gathers on the horizon! Your ratkin are ready!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Fill our bellies and we will crush the rotten-toothed geezer for you!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: When I said better guard-rats, I meant better than this, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: Sin-ts-ts-ts-e you refused me parley, I de-ts-ts-ts-ided to grant myself one.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: I urge you to re-ts-ts-ts-onsider, War Ts-ts-ts-ef! Many more lives will be lost!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: Give up your arms. Otherwise, my for-ts-ts-ts-es will ts-ts-ts-rush on the field of battle!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: There is only one Golden Cauldron and I intend to claim it.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: That's the worst offer in the history of offers!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: How about you re-ts-ts-ts-onsider?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: I will not be ridi-ts-ts-ts-uled!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: You will never see sense. Very well.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: You would make a terrible Rat King.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: A battle it is then.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: My Lord! Our scouts have returned. Mount Ratarat lies just north. But take heed, my Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: A host of moblings bearing the crest of spoon and knife marches to attack us!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: The mobling leader is a fool. The march will exhaust them, make them weak.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Only moblings? We will crush them!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Spoon and knife. Who does this crest belong to, General?

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Easy prey, my Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: No doubt, my Lord! But...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Eeeer... Glut Rattan, my Lord! The fattest of War Chefs, saviour of all the underfed and undefended moblings! Or so they say, Lord.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Or, at least, easier prey.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Glut Rattan leads this throng of moblings. We should be careful.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: His moblings love 'im my Lord, and will fight tooth and nail for him.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: And, and...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: There are only moblings in our horde, my Lord! For now.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: But feed them well, yes, and they will rip and tear your enemies!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Where's the rest of my army?!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Moblings are enough. Summon the troops!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: To the feeding grounds! Battle awaits!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Our stabby-rats are de-delayed, my Lord! Lost their way from your holdings!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Surely, they will join us soon! Matter of time, just!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Our moblings are not as strong as Glut's Lord, but we can overwhelm 'em with numbers!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Quantity trumps quality!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: A glorious victory, my Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Our tide of moblings has forced Rattan to withdraw his horde.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: And Rattapurna's grace blooms on us! While we battled, a crowd of our stabby-rats joined our host, bringing a wagon of food!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Nothing can stop us! The Golden Cauldron will be mine! I mean... Yours, my Lord! Yours!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: How did you defeat me, I wonder?Such imbeciles giving you counsel.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Trusting to a fault. Will be your undoing!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Ratso might be an imbecile, but he's my imbecile.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Rattan! Came for another round of sour-tasting defeat?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: General Ratso, remind me to execute some guards.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: This you who will chew the dirt!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: Executed them for you! Now, your turn. To die!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000017C
Properties.Text: My horde of moblings grows beyond number! Meet me on the field of battle, War Chef!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: Enemy archers want to join your camp

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: to battle!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: nah, no archers, i like stabby stabby

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: hell nah who needs 'em we can train archers ourselves

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: cool

Properties.Speaker: 0x0000000000000000
Properties.Text: War Chef 3: Battle 3

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Your lack of ambition is what prevents you from becoming somebody, General. We will loot both of those caravans!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Our ratkin needs more speed! Send troops to claim the Celery Quartz caravan!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: If my army hits faster, it kills faster. I want the Crackling Moss!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: And the best thing, Lord? If we act now and send troops, we would be able to loot only one of those caravans!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: The other wagon was loaded with Celery Quartz, a Spice that would make our troops run as fast as the wind!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: From the reports, one of them was filled with Crackling Moss that would give our troops attacks fast like strikes of lightning!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: They've seen Hood's forces loading them with a treasure in Spices, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: My Lord! Our scoutlings have seen two caravans escaping after the battle!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Another victory against the once-mighty Field Marshal! Might be his brains started rotting away after his teeth...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Victories link like spicy sausages, my Lord! The cauldron will surely be ours!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yours, Lord, only yours!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: My Lord! Dire news from the camp.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Forgive the interruption, my Lord! Some of the Field Marshal troops approach!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Your ambition is getting tedious, General. Control yourself.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: You know, General, sharp knives have a tendency to end in ratkin's back this time of the year...

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Betray me General and I'll use you as fuel for the Cauldron's fire pit.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Eeeek! I never did like fire, Lord...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: They do my lord, they do. And I have an acute allergy to cold, sharp steel!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Thousand apologies my Lord! A rat dream... But never act. Never!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Forgive your most trusted servant, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Many of our ratkin are sick to death! It's like a competition of who can throw up more, or farther away!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Our army is in shambles, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: So, the Bog Hard-Weed was spoiled...

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Or poisoned intentionally by the Field Marshal.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: I blame this on you, General.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Rattapurna's milk flows on us! We cannot lose, even if we had a single mobling left to fight!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: But my Lord, I am blameless! It was your decision to use the Weed!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Maybe the old fool isn't as rotten-brained as I thought!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yes! The Cauldron will be mine!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: You have led us this far, Lord! We fight for you until we can fight no more!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord! Some of the Field Marshal troops approach us, leaderless!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Lord! Lord! We plead, we beg! We are defeated again and again!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Toothsy is a brainless old fool! Lead us, War Chef Lord! Gifts we bring, gifts so you lead us!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Welcome, stabby-rats! My army could always use more shields.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Food is always the best gift, warriors!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: That Bog Hard-Weed is nasty, but it brings victory! Do you have more of the spice?

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Food we have Lord! What is ours is yours, by Rattapurna's tits!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: You won't regret this, Lord! We feast, we fight, we kill. For you!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Weed of the Bog, hardened! Yes, half a pellet, Lord! We would never come empty handed, no no!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord, Lord! Field Marshal Toothsy is here! I killed too many guards, no-one kept watch...

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: I see you have a-ts-ts-ts-epted strays from my army into yours!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: It was my duty as the offi-ts-ts-ts-er of the realm to parley on-ts-ts-ts-e more with you.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: Meet me on the field of battle, and be ts-ts-ts-rushed!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Do not listen to doddering fool, Lord! His forces are spent, wasted in previous fights!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000052E
Properties.Text: Attack now. Kill them all!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000379
Properties.Text: Will you really trust the words of a traitor, War Chef?

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Most wise, my Lord! Troops were just waiting for your word!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Fast like the winds, Lord! Troops were just waiting for your go-ahead.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: But, Lord... Both?

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: No! Your will will be done, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000008D7
Properties.Text: SOME TIME LATER

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000008D7
Properties.Text: SOME TIME LATER

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000008D7
Properties.Text: SOME TIME LATER

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord! Our troops were successful! Sacks of Crackling Moss are ours!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord! Troops have returned with Celery Quartz in tow!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Dire news, Lord... Our troops were slow to assemble in such numbers. Both caravans escaped.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: And to sour the milk from Rattapurna's tits even more, a number of raktin has died in the attack...

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: Lord! Tree banners are seen on the horizon!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: Army of Rattin Hood assembles to attack!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Lord! Spare the lives of moblings that fought for Toothsy!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: The old fool wanted to boil us alive if we didn't fight. Dying by the sword was better than that!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Now, we will fight for you, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: To show we are true, we brought food, Lord! Two wagons.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: More warriors are always welcome! You will feed from my cauldron.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Lord! Some of Toothsy's forces have come to plead with you!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Go away while you still have the chance.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Thank you for the food. Enjoy dying!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: But, no! Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Clever my Lord! They could've been spies for one of the remaining War Chefs.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: You never know who you can trust these days!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: But, but...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: You heard the Lord! Move it or die!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000293
Properties.Text: Lord is kind and wise! Rattapurna's bosom will shower you with milk of plenty!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Yes, yes, very kind, much excitement.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Now my Lord! Our scouts have seen another army moving in the area. It bears the tree crest on a green field!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: I'm sure that sounded like gibberish to you, Lord! That is the banner of Rattin Hood, the outlaw War Chef!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: The army of Rattin Hood the outlaw War Chef must be lurking nearby!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: I could order some scoutlings to search for them, learn of any weakness they have. But, that will costs provisions.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: You are full of excellent ideas, General. Yes, let us do so.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Send just a few. I don't want to waste precious food.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: The army is crushing my enemies. That food is better spent on more warriors.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: As you see fit, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Right you are Lord! A few scoutlings will attract even less attention.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Thank you, Lord, live to serve!

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: Yer no' the only one who can send spies. But if you want to do somethin' right, you got to do it yerself.

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: I really shouldn't have killed so much of our guards...

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: Your imbecile is correct, fellow War Chef.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: Sneaking around is not good for your health, Rattin.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: I presume you came here to ask me to surrender, avoid bloodshed?

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000003
Properties.Text: You just signed your own death warrant, moss-rat!

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: Rattapurna's tits, no! I came here to see your army.

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: And I have learned all that I need. A word of warning...

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: The sky looks dark, might rain a lot of iron later. See you on the field!

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: An arrow to the eye is even worse! And a word of warning...

Properties.Speaker: 0x01000003000006F8
Properties.Text: You'll have to defeat my army first! A word of warning...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Before you say anything Lord, I'll make sure we post even more guards around the camp!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: Lord! Scouting party reporting.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: My Lord! Scouts reporting! We sneaked into the enemy camp, Lord!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: There were too few us of to get close to the enemy camp. They shout us down like squirrels in a barrel...

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Banners of Rattin Hood are on the horizon, Lord! We must prepare.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: There's so many archers Lord, more than I can count. They will hide the sun when they shoot!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: We should send as many moblings as we can Lord! Our stabby-rats are slowed by their armor, they will be ripped to shreds by enemy arrows!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: Sure, some moblings will die during the charge, but they will close the distance quickly!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: The Field Marshal is dead lord, trampled to death by our ratkin!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: With all those rain-of-arrows threats, I expected to be a pincushion by now!

Properties.Speaker: 0x010000030000009C
Properties.Text: But here we are. Many Hood's ratkin dead, zero pincushions. Well... Zero General pincushions, that is.

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000700
Properties.Text: Lord! Lord! Enemy forces approach the camp bearing a surrender flag!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000973
Properties.Text: Lord War Chef! We left that thief-scoundrel Rattin Hood are looking for a new master!

Properties.Speaker: 0x0100000300000973
Properties.Text: We ask only to be fed, Lord, and we will rain death for you with our shooties!
